# Card-Based User Management System — Implementation Plan

## Summary
Replace the flat users table in the Admin Users view with a card-grid of expandable grouped lists. The table is removed entirely; all existing JS logic (filters, approveUser, changeRole, openUserDetails) is preserved and reused.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Component 1 — HTML (`admin.html`, lines 187–248)

#### [MODIFY] admin.html — Replace Users View HTML

Remove the current table + filter panel structure and replace with:

1. **Page header** (unchanged): title + search + filter button remain.
2. **Filter panel** (unchanged): role & status chips still live here.
3. **Group Cards Grid**: a `<div class="user-group-grid">` containing 4 static group cards:
   - ✅ Approved Users
   - ⏳ Pending Approval
   - 🔧 Organizers
   - 👥 Customers
4. **Service Subscriber Groups**: a `<div id="service-groups-grid">` populated dynamically by JS.
5. **Hidden `#users-tbody` `<table>`**: kept as a zero-size element so `renderUsersTableData` still writes to it without errors (backward compatibility).

Each group card:
```html
<div class="user-group-card" data-group="approved">
  <div class="user-group-card-header">
    <span class="group-icon">✅</span>
    <div class="group-info">
      <div class="group-title">Approved Users</div>
      <div class="group-subtitle" id="count-approved">— users</div>
    </div>
    <span class="group-arrow">▶</span>
  </div>
  <div class="user-group-list" id="list-approved"><!-- JS renders rows here --></div>
</div>
```

#### Scoped CSS added in `<style>` block

```css
.user-group-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; }
.user-group-card { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden; transition: box-shadow .2s; }
.user-group-card:hover { box-shadow: var(--shadow); }
.user-group-card-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem; cursor: pointer; }
.user-group-list { display: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 0; }
.user-group-card.open .user-group-list { display: block; }
.user-group-card.open .group-arrow { transform: rotate(90deg); }
.group-arrow { transition: transform .2s; margin-left: auto; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: .9rem; }
.user-row-card { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; align-items: center; padding: .85rem 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
.user-row-card:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
@media (max-width: 600px) { .user-group-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .user-row-card { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; } }
```

